node.text:
Video tour of The Syshaus designed by @studio.arthurcasas.

The Syshaus is the future of housing. It is a concept with constructive system with a standardized 1.2m grid system that allows the house to be built within 6 months. The keywords are quality, practicality, and sustainability, and eliminates the hassle of constructing a house.

node.text:
New tour on YouTube! 😍
We have visited @thenordicbarnhouseproject to tour Villa Brink which is an idyllic barnhouse nestled in a vibrant forest outside the Danish town of Randers. With a strong emphasis on natural materials simulating its natural context, the house beautifully balances the cold and the warm to create an atmospheric home for the designer’s own family. Here, one can experience the essence of Nordic bathhouse design; interact with the goats; eat a home-made egg; and relax in the shadow created by the generous trees. The house is designed by @brunojakobsendesign. Link in bio!

node.text:
Describe this home in ONE word! 💚
The Belanda House is a home where the experience of verticality trumps horizontality. The total of seven staircases threads the spaces together, and allows different experiences depending on which level you are on. The material palette was muted to contrast with the rich, emerald hues of the surrounding jungle. The house is designed by 29 Design and is located in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia // Photos by Lin Ho.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Who’d you bring? 😍
The Cosmos Villa is a modernist eco villa positioned high on the hillside and cantilevered to embrace the panoramic views of the Caribbean Sea. The design of the villa has great emphasis on sustainability as it is powered by solar energy, rainwater is harvested and recycled, and the pool is purified with a salt water ozone system. The eco retreat is located in Soufriere, St Lucia // Video by @dreamworld.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

What do you think? 😍
The Brick House is a duplex home aiming to combine the Iranian culture with modern architecture. Through a monumental brick facade of both straight, twisted and curved lines, the home presents an aesthetic that is diverse yet balanced. The house is designed by @ivan.architects and is being built in Golestan, Iran. 

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

The Phú Yên House is a summer retreat on the Vietnamese countryside for a family with children. The space of the bedroom and living room, kitchen and dining room are separated, and linked together by a green courtyard, making the spaces in the house airy and accessible. With the best nature, the yard and green spaces also become a fun area for the children and their friends. It is designed by Story Architecture and is located in Phu Yen, Vietnam // Photos by @minqbui.photography.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥

node.text:
Who’d you bring? 😍
The Hideout Horizon is a truly magical off-grid eco bamboo home hidden in the Balinese jungles high up in the mountains of Gunung Agung volcano. Due to its remote location, it is situated far away from the city life and therefore perfect for adventurous souls. The all-bamboo house has two floors including a breezy outdoor living area with a hammock, a wardrobe, a bathroom, and a beautiful authentic pool. @hideoutbali is (as indicated) located in the eastern part of Bali near the volcano, Mount Agung. // Photos by @thefreedomcomplex and video by @peppers_passport + @conceptsean.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!

node.text:
Who’d you bring? 💚
Constructed as a movie set for the Lord of the Rings movies, Hobbiton displays a soulful type of vernacular architecture giving life to organic, circular shapes that follows Matamata’s grassy hills of the northern part of New Zealand. In regular urban and suburban areas, we tend to live in boxes; most of them being rather identical. Hobbiton therefore proposes a great alternative and an example of what architecture can become to allow an immersive experience of nature. // Photos by @shaun_jeffers.

Watch more house tours on our new YouTube channel. 🎥
Link in bio!
